Benefits of not pre-selecting checkboxes:
User Experience: Users only select what they need, leading to fewer overall interactions. This avoids the inconvenience of having to deselect options that are not relevant to them.

Performance: As you've mentioned, deselecting all options can cause a performance hit. By not pre-selecting, you can avoid this lag altogether.

Clarity: When a user lands on the page, it's clear that no filters or selections have
